Revolvers!

261
00:34:20,541 --> 00:34:23,738
Here's where I keep the best ones.

262
00:34:28,750 --> 00:34:31,617
Remington, Colt, Farroute...

263
00:34:32,920 --> 00:34:35,889
...Smith Wesson, Colt, from the Navy...

264
00:34:37,258 --> 00:34:40,523
Jocelyn, another Remington, and this...

265
00:34:40,995 --> 00:34:42,826
That's enough.

266
00:35:25,606 --> 00:35:27,699
Cartridges.

267
00:35:35,917 --> 00:35:39,045
- You wanna try the pistol, just step...
- Let's go.

268
00:37:02,236 --> 00:37:04,261
Cartridge.

269
00:37:12,079 --> 00:37:13,171
How much?

270
00:37:13,247 --> 00:37:15,112
$20.

271
00:37:22,023 --> 00:37:23,854
$50.

272
00:37:25,159 --> 00:37:26,956
How much?

273
00:37:27,328 --> 00:37:29,319
$100.

274
00:37:31,966 --> 00:37:35,026
$200. It's all I've got!

275
00:37:56,857 --> 00:37:58,347
Come here!

276
00:38:28,589 --> 00:38:30,352
This morning I heard the whole thing.

277
00:38:30,424 --> 00:38:32,654
They say Colonel Canby's closing in
with his Northerners...

278
00:38:32,727 --> 00:38:35,560
...and no later than tomorrow
that they'll be in the city.

279
00:38:35,629 --> 00:38:38,621
That's why these Southerners
are getting out!

280
00:38:38,699 --> 00:38:42,965
You see, as soon as these cowards hear
there are blue shirts around, they run.

281
00:38:43,037 --> 00:38:45,972
- These rebels have no will to fight!
- Poor things.

282
00:38:46,040 --> 00:38:47,632
They'll soon be finished.

283
00:38:47,708 --> 00:38:48,868
We get rid of these bastards...

284
00:38:48,943 --> 00:38:51,377
...then we begin making money
on those Yankees.

285
00:38:51,445 --> 00:38:55,677
They carry gold, not paper dollars.
And they're going to beat the South.

286
00:38:56,884 --> 00:39:00,081
Look, see that one with the white beard
sitting in the wagon?

287
00:39:00,154 --> 00:39:03,988
General Sibley. He looks dead.
He's finally getting out of our hair.

288
00:39:04,058 --> 00:39:07,027
Hooray for Dixie!
Hooray, hooray for Dixie!

289
00:39:12,767 --> 00:39:15,258
Where's the owner of that horse?

290
00:39:15,836 --> 00:39:17,030
Please, mister, sir...

291
00:39:17,104 --> 00:39:19,129
...a bad heart condition...
- Where?

292
00:39:19,206 --> 00:39:21,674
The war has frightened me already.

293
00:39:21,976 --> 00:39:24,376
I'm looking for the owner of that horse.

294
00:39:24,445 --> 00:39:27,676
He's tall, blond, he smokes a cigar,
and he's a pig!

