302
00:39:28,115 --> 00:39:29,377
Where is he now?!

303
00:39:29,450 --> 00:39:32,317
You leave him be! He doesn't know
who rides every horse!

304
00:39:32,386 --> 00:39:35,184
You stay quiet, old hen!

305
00:39:36,424 --> 00:39:39,757
Upstairs. Upstairs, in Room 4, señor.

306
00:39:45,466 --> 00:39:46,933
Hear that?

307
00:39:52,406 --> 00:39:55,398
You rotten criminals, how dare you?!

308
00:42:53,053 --> 00:42:54,816
Your spurs.

309
00:43:07,034 --> 00:43:09,764
There are two kinds of spurs, my friend.

310
00:43:09,837 --> 00:43:12,738
Those that come in by the door...

311
00:43:12,806 --> 00:43:15,331
...and those that come in by the window.

312
00:43:15,409 --> 00:43:17,775
Take off that pistol belt.

313
00:43:25,119 --> 00:43:27,053
It's empty.

314
00:43:29,189 --> 00:43:31,180
Mine isn't.

315
00:43:37,264 --> 00:43:41,223
Even when Judas hanged himself,
there was a storm, too.

316
00:43:44,605 --> 00:43:47,073
That could be cannon fire.

317
00:43:47,141 --> 00:43:50,702
Cannon fire or storm,
it's all the same to you!

318
00:43:53,013 --> 00:43:55,811
You ever see this before, my friend?

319
00:44:04,925 --> 00:44:07,553
Throw it over the roof beam.

320
00:44:09,396 --> 00:44:11,421
That's it.

321
00:44:22,443 --> 00:44:24,570
And get on that!

322
00:44:34,321 --> 00:44:36,084
That's right.

323
00:44:36,156 --> 00:44:38,590
Now, make sure the rope is tight!

324
00:44:38,892 --> 00:44:41,827
It's got to hold the weight of a pig!

325
00:44:48,001 --> 00:44:50,834
Now, put the rope around your neck!

326
00:44:57,444 --> 00:44:59,469
Yes, very good.

327
00:45:00,481 --> 00:45:02,540
It's too big for your neck?

328
00:45:02,616 --> 00:45:04,550
We'll fix that right away.

329
00:45:04,618 --> 00:45:06,313
I have another system.

330
00:45:06,387 --> 00:45:09,185
A little different than yours.

331
00:45:09,423 --> 00:45:11,414
I don't shoot the rope.

332
00:45:11,492 --> 00:45:13,824
I shoot the legs off the stool!

333
00:45:18,265 --> 00:45:19,926
Adiós.

334
00:48:21,848 --> 00:48:25,375
...guilty of the following crimes:
horse theft...

335
00:48:43,804 --> 00:48:45,931
And Shorty?

336
00:49:09,396 --> 00:49:11,523
Sorry, Shorty!

337
00:49:12,366 --> 00:49:14,800
Move, come on, let's go!

338
00:49:39,326 --> 00:49:42,557
I don't know. As soon as I hit
the desert, I'm thirsty.

339
00:49:42,829 --> 00:49:43,989
Burns, huh?

340
00:49:44,064 --> 00:49:47,830
They say people with fair skin
can't take too much.

341
00:50:12,159 --> 00:50:15,492
Like that, you won't
have to carry so much.

342
00:50:16,830 --> 00:50:18,798
Where are we going?

343
00:50:19,199 --> 00:50:20,461
Where?

344
00:50:20,534 --> 00:50:22,900
Where I'm going, amigo.

345
00:50:23,670 --> 00:50:25,194
Over that way.

346
00:50:25,272 --> 00:50:28,730
Another 100 miles
of beautiful sunbaked sand.

347
00:50:29,543 --> 00:50:31,909
Even the armies are afraid
to march through there.

348
00:50:31,978 --> 00:50:34,276
Sibley's men are retreating up there.

349
00:50:34,381 --> 00:50:37,111
Canby's men are coming here...

350
00:50:37,718 --> 00:50:41,119
...but no one will set foot in this hell...

351
00:50:42,055 --> 00:50:44,489
...except you and me.

352
00:50:45,992 --> 00:50:49,189
One hundred miles. That's a nice walk.

353
00:50:51,665 --> 00:50:54,793
What was it you told me the last time?

354
00:50:56,269 --> 00:51:00,467
"If you save your breath,
I feel a man like you could manage it."

355
00:51:02,275 --> 00:51:05,335
And if you won't manage it, you'll die.

356
00:51:05,412 --> 00:51:06,936
Only slowly.

357
00:51:08,048 --> 00:51:10,516
Very slowly, old friend.

358
00:51:15,789 --> 00:51:18,690
After you, please. Start walking.

359
00:53:15,141 --> 00:53:17,234
Taking a rest?

360
00:53:17,711 --> 00:53:22,080
Come on, Blondie, we don't have
very far to go. Only 70 miles.

361
00:53:23,583 --> 00:53:27,212
Only eight and a half hours more
before sunset.

362
00:53:27,354 --> 00:53:29,652
That's not too bad.

363
00:53:30,724 --> 00:53:32,521
Come on!

364
00:55:35,749 --> 00:55:37,683
And so, Blondie...

365
00:55:39,953 --> 00:55:41,978
...it's goodbye.

366
00:59:28,248 --> 00:59:31,877
$200,000 in gold. It's yours.
Just get me water!

367
00:59:37,190 --> 00:59:39,385
What's that you say?

368
00:59:39,459 --> 00:59:40,983
Who the hell are you?

369
00:59:43,396 --> 00:59:45,762
My name's Bill Carson now.

370
00:59:46,666 --> 00:59:48,258
Surprise attack.

371
00:59:50,103 --> 00:59:51,035
All dead.

372
00:59:51,104 --> 00:59:54,198
My name is Jackson. Not Carson.

373
00:59:54,574 --> 00:59:56,439
Yeah, yeah, glad to meet you, Carson.

374
00:59:56,509 --> 01:00:00,104
I'm Lincoln's grandfather.
What was that you said about the dollars?

375
01:00:00,179 --> 01:00:02,272
$200,000, all mine.

376
01:00:03,516 --> 01:00:06,110
Was the Third Cavalry's.

377
01:00:06,552 --> 01:00:08,645
Baker has nothing.

378
01:00:09,255 --> 01:00:10,415
The gold...

379
01:00:10,490 --> 01:00:13,425
I hid the gold. The gold is safe!

380
01:00:14,193 --> 01:00:16,058
Where? Here?

381
01:00:17,363 --> 01:00:19,092
Talk!

382
01:00:19,565 --> 01:00:21,624
In the cemetery.

383
01:00:21,701 --> 01:00:23,692
Which cemetery?

384
01:00:24,771 --> 01:00:27,103
On Sad Hill.

385
01:00:27,173 --> 01:00:29,004
There's a grave by the...

386
01:00:29,842 --> 01:00:31,332
Which grave?

387
01:00:31,411 --> 01:00:33,879
Have a name? Have a number?

388
01:00:33,946 --> 01:00:36,346
Come on, you dummy, talk!

389
01:00:37,984 --> 01:00:40,248
There's no number.

390
01:00:40,687 --> 01:00:42,177
There's a name.

391
01:00:43,356 --> 01:00:45,551
It's written.

392
01:00:52,165 --> 01:00:53,462
Water!

393
01:00:56,235 --> 01:00:59,033
You talk first, eh?
I'll give you the water later!

394
01:00:59,172 --> 01:01:00,867
Sad Hill Cemetery, okay?

395
01:01:00,973 --> 01:01:02,201
In a grave, okay.

396
01:01:02,275 --> 01:01:04,869
But it must have
a name or a number on it.

397
01:01:04,977 --> 01:01:07,969
There must be 1,000, 5,000, you!

398
01:01:11,851 --> 01:01:13,751
Don't die.

399
01:01:13,820 --> 01:01:16,186
Don't die! I'll get you water!

400
01:01:16,289 --> 01:01:19,656
Stay there.
Don't move, I'll get you water.

401
01:01:19,726 --> 01:01:22,092
Don't die until later!

402
01:01:47,820 --> 01:01:49,117
Get away from there!

403
01:01:55,661 --> 01:01:57,424
He's dead.

404
01:02:01,033 --> 01:02:02,796
I'll kill you!

405
01:02:05,238 --> 01:02:08,435
If you do that, you'll always be poor.

406
01:02:09,509 --> 01:02:12,706
Just like the greasy rat that you are.

407
01:02:13,146 --> 01:02:15,307
If I were you, I'd...

408
01:02:15,548 --> 01:02:17,209
...keep me alive.

409
01:02:17,483 --> 01:02:19,815
What did he tell you?

410
01:02:20,853 --> 01:02:22,013
A name.

411
01:02:23,256 --> 01:02:25,087
Name on a grave.

412
01:02:25,324 --> 01:02:27,019
What name?

413
01:02:40,773 --> 01:02:42,866
Blondie, don't die.

414
01:02:43,943 --> 01:02:46,411
Don't die! I'm your friend.

415
01:02:46,646 --> 01:02:50,241
Please don't die. Please! I'm your friend!

416
01:02:53,586 --> 01:02:55,747
I'll help you. I'll help you!

417
01:02:55,822 --> 01:02:58,791
Don't move. I'll be right back.
I'll get the water.

418
01:02:58,858 --> 01:03:01,326
Don't die like that pig.

419
01:03:02,862 --> 01:03:04,523
Water, Blondie?

420
01:03:04,597 --> 01:03:06,622
Don't drink! It's no good for you.

421
01:03:06,699 --> 01:03:08,599
Feel better?

422
01:03:08,668 --> 01:03:12,365
Blondie, what's the matter?
Please don't die!

423
01:03:41,133 --> 01:03:42,430
I've got a very sick man here.

424
01:03:42,502 --> 01:03:43,992
But we have no more beds here.

425
01:03:44,070 --> 01:03:46,470
Let him have yours!

426
01:03:51,677 --> 01:03:53,975
- Where is Pablo Ramirez?
- Padre Ramirez.

427
01:03:54,046 --> 01:03:55,707
He is away at the moment.

428
01:03:55,948 --> 01:03:58,314
He should be back any day now.

429
01:03:58,417 --> 01:04:02,854
It doesn't matter. For the moment,
we'll take very good care of my friend.

430
01:04:02,955 --> 01:04:04,513
May God be praised.

431
01:04:04,590 --> 01:04:05,818
In case you didn't know it...

432
01:04:05,892 --> 01:04:09,760
...God is on our side, too.
Because he hates the Yanks.

433
01:04:11,497 --> 01:04:12,930
Father, is he still breathing?

434
01:04:12,999 --> 01:04:15,126
Yes, of course.

435
01:04:15,768 --> 01:04:17,668
You're heavy.

436
01:04:59,545 --> 01:05:02,480
All right, put a fresh bandage on him.

437
01:05:03,449 --> 01:05:05,679
Put him in my cell.

438
01:05:10,723 --> 01:05:13,123
Out, soldier. Out you go, come on.

439
01:05:13,225 --> 01:05:17,252
Look out for him, please.
He's like a brother to me!

440
01:05:36,248 --> 01:05:39,046
Father, did he speak?
Did he say anything?

441
01:06:09,415 --> 01:06:12,077
Did he ask for me?
Did he speak about anything?

442
01:06:12,151 --> 01:06:14,915
No, he hasn't spoken as yet.
But you mustn't worry.

443
01:06:14,987 --> 01:06:18,855
He's both young and strong.
That's what's kept him going until now.

444
01:06:19,025 --> 01:06:21,755
He should regain his strength
in a very short time.

445
01:06:21,827 --> 01:06:26,059
Thank you, Father. You don't know
how much this boy's life means to me!

446
01:07:44,810 --> 01:07:48,541
The old Father tells me
you'll be up and around in a few days.

447
01:07:48,748 --> 01:07:52,115
You're very lucky to have me
so close when it happened.

448
01:07:52,451 --> 01:07:54,851
Think, if you'd been on your own.

449
01:07:57,223 --> 01:07:58,781
I mean, when...

450
01:07:58,858 --> 01:08:01,326
...when one is ill...

451
01:08:01,660 --> 01:08:05,096
...it's good to have somebody close by,
friends or relations.

452
01:08:07,166 --> 01:08:08,690
Do you...

453
01:08:08,768 --> 01:08:10,963
...you have parents, Blondie?

454
01:08:11,437 --> 01:08:12,927
A mother?

455
01:08:13,005 --> 01:08:15,269
Not even a mother.

456
01:08:16,008 --> 01:08:17,305
No one.

457
01:08:18,210 --> 01:08:21,043
You're all alone, huh? Like me, Blondie.

458
01:08:21,714 --> 01:08:24,444
We're all alone in the world.

459
01:08:24,517 --> 01:08:26,508
I have you, you have me.

460
01:08:29,588 --> 01:08:31,920
Only for a little while, I mean.

461
01:08:32,291 --> 01:08:34,225
It had to happen now.

462
01:08:34,927 --> 01:08:37,395
What a dirty rotten trick of fate!

463
01:08:37,463 --> 01:08:40,591
We could have all that money
in our hands.

464
01:08:46,972 --> 01:08:49,532
I must tell you the truth, Blondie.

465
01:08:49,642 --> 01:08:52,839
In my place, you would do the same thing.

466
01:08:54,313 --> 01:08:56,543
It's all over for you now.

467
01:08:57,249 --> 01:09:00,218
There's nothing anyone can do anymore.

468
01:09:04,356 --> 01:09:06,654
It's my fault! Mine, mine!

469
01:09:19,305 --> 01:09:23,173
I'll tell you one thing, Blondie.
If I knew that my last hour had come...

470
01:09:23,242 --> 01:09:27,679
...I swear, in my place, in your place,
I would do the same thing.

471
01:09:28,914 --> 01:09:32,179
I would tell about the gold.
Yes, yes I would!

472
01:09:32,284 --> 01:09:34,752
I would tell the name on the grave.

473
01:09:34,820 --> 01:09:37,516
After all, what good is the money to you
if you're dead?

474
01:09:37,590 --> 01:09:39,649
I know the name of the cemetery.

475
01:09:39,725 --> 01:09:42,853
But you know how many graves
there are there?

476
01:09:42,928 --> 01:09:44,122
Please.

477
01:09:46,232 --> 01:09:48,200
Please, have a little.

478
01:09:51,503 --> 01:09:54,472
Coffee? Please tell me the name.

479
01:09:56,542 --> 01:09:58,066
On the grave.

480
01:09:58,911 --> 01:10:01,903
If I get my hands on the $200,000...

481
01:10:03,749 --> 01:10:06,343
...I'll always honor your memory.

482
01:10:06,819 --> 01:10:09,947
I swear it! I'll always honor your memory!

483
01:10:13,025 --> 01:10:14,993
Come closer.

484
01:10:19,999 --> 01:10:21,091
Tell me.

485
01:10:26,705 --> 01:10:29,003
I'll sleep better...

486
01:10:30,276 --> 01:10:32,870
...knowing my good friend...

487
01:10:33,112 --> 01:10:35,137
...is by my side...

488
01:10:35,214 --> 01:10:36,738
...to protect me.

489
01:10:47,426 --> 01:10:49,758
"Tuco, water. Please, water."

490
01:10:49,862 --> 01:10:53,389
But if I get that name from you,
I'll give you water!

491
01:11:00,539 --> 01:11:03,406
All right, you dirty skunk,
get your ass off the bed!

492
01:11:03,475 --> 01:11:05,602
Come on, come on, the party's over.

493
01:11:05,678 --> 01:11:07,407
The wagon is all ready to go.

494
01:11:07,513 --> 01:11:09,572
From the way the wounded
are pouring into this place...

495
01:11:09,648 --> 01:11:12,913
...we better get the hell out of here
before we get caught up in the war.

496
01:11:12,985 --> 01:11:15,886
Tuco, Father Ramirez is back.

497
01:11:16,088 --> 01:11:20,548
This is something I have to look into.
It'll only take a minute. Get moving.

498
01:11:20,693 --> 01:11:22,320
- Where? This way?
- Yes.

499
01:11:40,079 --> 01:11:41,171
Hey, Pablo!

500
01:11:49,621 --> 01:11:51,851
Don't you recognize me?

501
01:11:53,359 --> 01:11:55,088
It's me, Tuco!

502
01:11:55,694 --> 01:11:58,026
Let me embrace you.

503
01:12:00,866 --> 01:12:03,801
I don't know the right thing!

504
01:12:08,207 --> 01:12:10,471
I was just passing by here.
I said to myself...

505
01:12:10,542 --> 01:12:14,376
...I wonder if my brother
remembers his brother.

506
01:12:17,049 --> 01:12:18,880
Did I do wrong?

507
01:12:19,952 --> 01:12:22,580
It doesn't matter. I'm very happy.

508
01:12:22,654 --> 01:12:24,952
You've seen me, Tuco.

509
01:12:26,925 --> 01:12:29,519
Yeah, well, I'm very glad I came.

510
01:12:35,367 --> 01:12:38,302
Oh, my uniform. It's a long story.

511
01:12:39,538 --> 01:12:42,803
Let's talk about you. It's more important.

512
01:12:43,308 --> 01:12:45,139
You look very well.

513
01:12:45,444 --> 01:12:48,106
A bit thin, perhaps, but...

514
01:12:49,381 --> 01:12:52,350
...you always were thin, eh Pablito?

515
01:12:55,387 --> 01:12:57,446
What about our parents?

516
01:12:58,690 --> 01:13:00,954
Only now do you think of them?

517
01:13:02,127 --> 01:13:04,152
To begin after nine years?

518
01:13:06,365 --> 01:13:08,230
Nine years?

519
01:13:09,535 --> 01:13:10,968
So it's nine years.

520
01:13:14,506 --> 01:13:17,532
Our mother has been dead a long time.

521
01:13:18,744 --> 01:13:22,077
Our father died only a few days ago.

522
01:13:22,147 --> 01:13:24,047
That's why I was away.

523
01:13:25,918 --> 01:13:28,318
He asked for you to be there.

524
01:13:28,387 --> 01:13:30,719
But there was only me.

525
01:13:37,529 --> 01:13:39,554
And you?

526
01:13:39,631 --> 01:13:42,759
Outside of evil,
what else have you managed to do?

527
01:13:44,136 --> 01:13:47,628
It seems to me
you once had a wife someplace.

528
01:13:50,042 --> 01:13:52,101
Not one, lots of them!

529
01:13:52,177 --> 01:13:54,839
One here, one there,
wherever I found them.

530
01:13:56,048 --> 01:13:58,846
Go on, preach me a sermon, Pablo.

531
01:14:00,586 --> 01:14:02,918
What good would that be?

532
01:14:04,156 --> 01:14:06,624
Just keep on the way you're going.

533
01:14:06,692 --> 01:14:08,125
Go away.

534
01:14:09,561 --> 01:14:10,789
The Lord have mercy on your soul.

535
01:14:10,863 --> 01:14:14,458
I'll go, I'll go. While I'm waiting
for the Lord to remember me...

536
01:14:14,533 --> 01:14:18,196
...I., Tuco Ramirez,
brother of Brother Ramirez...

537
01:14:18,270 --> 01:14:20,261
...will tell you something.

538
01:14:20,339 --> 01:14:22,330
You think you're better than I am.

539
01:14:22,407 --> 01:14:25,069
Where we came from,
if one did not want to die of poverty...

540
01:14:25,144 --> 01:14:27,544
...one became a priest or a bandit!

541
01:14:27,613 --> 01:14:30,207
You chose your way, I chose mine.

542
01:14:30,282 --> 01:14:31,943
Mine was harder.

543
01:14:32,084 --> 01:14:33,813
You talk of our mother and father.

544
01:14:33,886 --> 01:14:36,013
You remember when you left
to become a priest.

545
01:14:36,088 --> 01:14:37,487
I stayed behind!

546
01:14:37,556 --> 01:14:41,390
I must have been ten, twelve.
I don't remember which, but I stayed.

547
01:14:41,460 --> 01:14:43,860
I tried, but it was no good.

548
01:14:43,929 --> 01:14:46,090
Now I am going to tell you something.

549
01:14:46,165 --> 01:14:47,689
You became a priest because you were...

550
01:14:47,766 --> 01:14:50,758
...too much of a coward to do what I do!

551
01:15:21,333 --> 01:15:23,563
Please, forgive me, brother.

552
01:15:53,265 --> 01:15:54,926
My belly's full.

553
01:15:56,768 --> 01:15:58,702
Nice guy, my brother.

554
01:15:59,071 --> 01:16:01,437
I didn't tell you
my brother was in charge here.

555
01:16:01,506 --> 01:16:03,701
Everything, like the pope almost.

556
01:16:03,775 --> 01:16:05,709
He's in charge in Rome.

557
01:16:05,777 --> 01:16:09,269
My brother, he says to me:
"Stay, brother, don't go home.

558
01:16:09,348 --> 01:16:11,111
"We never see each other.

559
01:16:11,183 --> 01:16:15,620
"Here, there's plenty to eat and drink.
Bring your friend, too."

560
01:16:15,687 --> 01:16:18,053
Whenever we see each other,
he never lets me go.

561
01:16:18,123 --> 01:16:20,523
It's always the same story.

562
01:16:20,592 --> 01:16:23,254
My brother, he's crazy about me.

563
01:16:27,099 --> 01:16:27,997
That's so.

564
01:16:28,066 --> 01:16:31,399
Even a tramp like me,
no matter what happens...

565
01:16:32,204 --> 01:16:37,699
...I know there's a brother somewhere
who will never refuse me a bowl of soup.

566
01:16:39,111 --> 01:16:40,510
Sure.

567
01:16:41,913 --> 01:16:45,849
Well, after a meal,
there's nothing like a good cigar.

568
01:17:53,852 --> 01:17:55,319
Wake up, you!

569
01:17:55,687 --> 01:17:57,120
The troops are coming!

570
01:17:57,189 --> 01:17:59,214
Blue or gray?

571
01:18:05,997 --> 01:18:10,457
They're gray like us. Let's say "hello"
to them and then get going.

572
01:18:11,203 --> 01:18:14,468
Hurrah for the Confederacy! Hurrah!

573
01:18:14,539 --> 01:18:16,598
Down with General Grant!

574
01:18:16,708 --> 01:18:19,609
Hurrah for General... what's his name?

575
01:18:19,678 --> 01:18:20,702
Lee!

576
01:18:22,748 --> 01:18:26,184
God is with us
because he hates the Yanks, too!

577
01:18:27,953 --> 01:18:31,719
God is not on our side
'cause he hates idiots also.

578
01:18:51,610 --> 01:18:53,237
Prisoners of war...

579
01:18:53,311 --> 01:18:55,006
...forward...

580
01:18:55,914 --> 01:18:57,108
...march!

581
01:19:59,911 --> 01:20:02,175
Form a single file.

582
01:21:01,940 --> 01:21:03,567
Robert Clark.

583
01:21:03,642 --> 01:21:04,870
Present.

584
01:21:05,844 --> 01:21:07,106
Sam Richmond.

585
01:21:07,178 --> 01:21:08,406
Present.

586
01:21:11,550 --> 01:21:13,017
Bill Carson.

587
01:21:19,291 --> 01:21:21,282
I said Bill Carson!

588
01:21:22,093 --> 01:21:24,994
Hey, Blondie, isn't that Angel Eyes?

589
01:21:25,530 --> 01:21:28,761
All right, what's he doing? Sleeping?!

590
01:21:31,636 --> 01:21:34,799
Yeah, and you better be Bill Carson.

591
01:21:37,809 --> 01:21:39,208
That's me!

592
01:21:47,552 --> 01:21:49,713
Please, Carson.

593
01:21:50,889 --> 01:21:52,618
Answer, "Present"!

594
01:21:54,259 --> 01:21:56,420
What are you, deaf?

595
01:22:02,100 --> 01:22:05,069
Now, suppose you say "present," Carson.

596
01:22:06,471 --> 01:22:09,372
I like big fat men like you.

597
01:22:09,441 --> 01:22:11,841
When they fall, they make more noise.

598
01:22:11,910 --> 01:22:14,470
And sometimes they never get up.

599
01:22:15,413 --> 01:22:17,278
Wallace...

600
01:22:18,783 --> 01:22:20,512
...that's enough.

601
01:22:23,154 --> 01:22:24,985
Sergeant!

602
01:22:26,524 --> 01:22:29,516
The captain wants to see you right away.

603
01:22:32,464 --> 01:22:35,297
Be sure these two get good treatment.

604
01:22:45,377 --> 01:22:49,006
Hey, Blondie, did you hear that?
Good treatment!

605
01:22:55,920 --> 01:22:58,411
For the last time, sergeant...

606
01:22:58,490 --> 01:22:59,582
...I'm telling you...

607
01:22:59,658 --> 01:23:02,752
...I want the prisoners
treated as prisoners.

608
01:23:03,495 --> 01:23:05,292
No more brutality!

609
01:23:06,398 --> 01:23:10,198
There's hundreds of prisoners out there
and only a few men to guard them.

610
01:23:10,268 --> 01:23:12,600
What am I supposed to do?
I have to have respect!

611
01:23:12,671 --> 01:23:17,506
I think that you'll manage to gain
their respect by treating them better!

612
01:23:18,877 --> 01:23:21,471
Are our men treated that well
in Andersonville Camp?

613
01:23:21,546 --> 01:23:24,310
I don't give a goddamn
what they do in Andersonville!

614
01:23:24,382 --> 01:23:26,714
While I'm in charge here,
the prisoners are not to be...

615
01:23:26,785 --> 01:23:27,911
...tortured...

616
01:23:27,986 --> 01:23:29,681
...or cheated...

617
01:23:29,988 --> 01:23:31,580
...or murdered!

618
01:23:31,890 --> 01:23:33,687
Is that an accusation?

619
01:23:33,758 --> 01:23:37,091
Sergeant, gangrene is eating
my leg away...

620
01:23:37,896 --> 01:23:39,523
...not my eyes.

621
01:23:39,597 --> 01:23:42,691
I know the prisoners here are being
robbed systematically.

622
01:23:42,767 --> 01:23:46,601
I know there's scum around,
or bivouacked near the camp, waiting...

623
01:23:46,671 --> 01:23:49,572
...for someone to deliver this loot.

624
01:23:49,641 --> 01:23:53,407
But as long as I'm commandant,
I won't permit any such trickery!

625
01:23:53,445 --> 01:23:55,037
Am I clear?

626
01:23:56,848 --> 01:23:58,145
Yes, sir.

627
01:23:58,316 --> 01:24:01,410
Just as long as you're the commandant.

628
01:24:02,487 --> 01:24:04,045
Yes, sergeant.

629
01:24:06,925 --> 01:24:10,258
I know this leg means
I won't last very long...

630
01:24:10,328 --> 01:24:13,195
...but I pray I can manage
to have enough time...

631
01:24:13,264 --> 01:24:18,258
...to amass evidence and bring to a
court-martial all those who discredit...

632
01:24:18,970 --> 01:24:21,564
...and dishonor the uniform...

633
01:24:21,806 --> 01:24:23,501
...of the Union!

634
01:24:27,746 --> 01:24:29,441
I wish you luck.

